Article 263 of the Constitution lays down the provisions for the Inter-State Council. We need to locate where this article mentions the body of people or the body of legislation that establishes this council.

### Step 2: Locate Article 263
Upon checking, Article 263 of the Constitution of India deals with the Inter-State Council and states that the Council shall consist of such number of officers, experts, and representatives as the President may, by notification, specify in this behalf. 

