<information>Doc 1: Philippe Perrin, born in 1955, is a French journalist and author. He is best known for his work on the French military interventions in Chad,
Doc 2: He served as the Minister of Defence from 2007 to 2010 and is currently the head of the Institut de Recherche et d'Etudes Stratégiques (IREST) in Paris.
Doc 3: His occupation was that of journalist, politician and public servant. After studying at the Lycée Carnot, he attended the École Nationale
Doc 4: Born in 1955, he graduated from the Ecole Nationale d'Administration in 1981 and has been a member of the National Assembly since 1993.
Doc 5: The author of The Last Empire, Philippe Perrin was also one of the most influential French journalists of the 1980s. He served as an MEP in 1994 and 1999.</information>

Based on these results, Philippe Perrin is a journalist and politician.

<answer>
